\title{Conjugacy Classes of a group}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-16}
\taxon{definition}
\MML{weddwitt}{def 3}{K3}

\p{Let #{G} be a [[gr-000G]]. We define the set of \define{Conjugacy Classes} of #{G} to be the set #{\{\Cl(g)\subset G\mid g\in G\}}.}
\p{Moreover, this forms a partition of #{G} in the sense that for any #{g\in G} there exists exactly one conjugacy class #{C} such that #{g\in C}. This is because #{g\in\Cl(g)} and for any #{h\in G} such that #{g\in\Cl(h)} must satisfy #{\Cl(g)=\Cl(h)} by [[gr-0044]].}